questions_and_answers = "[code]
[center][b][font_size=24]HudMod Video Editor[/font_size][/b][/center]

[b][color=#4db2ff]What is HudMod?[/color][/b]
HudMod is a video editor developed to fill the gap in its category of open-source software. It is designed to be flexible, easy, and efficient for most editors' requirements, specifically content creators.

[b][color=#4db2ff]Meaning Behind the Name?[/color][/b]
The name consists of two parts: [b]Hudhud Modify[/b], or [b]Hud-Mod[/b] for short.
\"هدهد\" in Arabic refers to the [b]Hoopoe[/b] bird, known for its agile and fast movement, and its association with wisdom in Arabic culture. The program's name is inspired by this beautiful bird, embodying its symbolic qualities and characteristics.

[b][color=#4db2ff]What HudMod Provides:[/color][/b]
HudMod offers a suite of competitive video software and systems, including:
[ul]
Support for [b]Real-time playback[/b] and instant preview.
Effects based on a [b]Component system[/b].
[b]Animation[/b] for all properties.
A fully integrated custom interface with [b]Multi-Monitor[/b].
[/ul]

[b][color=#4db2ff]Founding:[/color][/b]
[b]Founder:[/b] Omar Mohammed Balita.
A game and software developer who believes in the Godot Engine and a fully open-source future, working toward that goal, designed the program 99% of the way

[b]Core Contributor/s:[/b]
Malek Al-Ateeq.

[b][color=#4db2ff]Achieved Goals:[/color][/b]
[ul]
Providing a real-time editing environment.
Providing precise control over motion and effects.
Providing a clean and efficient user interface.
Maintaining high performance across various types of devices.
Building a substantial base of components/effects for the start.
[/ul]

[b][color=#4db2ff]Vision:[/color][/b]
Our current recorded goals include:
[ul]
Building the first stable version and presenting it to all users.
Primary focus on the [b]Linux[/b] platform, providing a fast download and workspace environment (to bridge the current gap in existing video editors).
Building a community of supporters to ensure sustainability (aiming to provide a modest monthly salary for those working on it).
[/ul]
You can review progress through blogs on [i][url={itch_link}]Itch[/url][/i], and communicate directly with developers to share your opinions via [i][url={discord_link}]Discord[/url][/i].

[b][color=#4db2ff]Challenges:[/color][/b]
The biggest challenge is establishing an independent financial support structure to ensure development [i][url={support_link}]Patreon[/url][/i].
The second challenge is the development mechanism, where any feature must pass through testing and stabilization before being released in a stable version (this does not apply to Alpha versions).

[b][color=#4db2ff]FAQ:[/color][/b]

[b]Q: Is HudMod Standalone?[/b]
A: Yes. HudMod is a standalone video editing application.

[b]Q: Do we use Godot?[/b]
A: HudMod is primarily built on the [b]Godot Engine[/b] for all rendering systems and integrated APIs, ensuring high performance and cross-platform compatibility.

[b]Q: Will professional editing tools be integrated into HudMod?[/b]
A: Of course. After working on core features and ensuring stability, the focus will shift toward professional tools based on priorities.

[b][color=#4db2ff]Message from the Founder:[/color][/b]
\"I hope we pay more attention to emerging open-source projects and give them a chance to compete with the giants. We are inspired by and follow in the footsteps of other inspiring projects like Blender and the Godot Engine.\"

For financial support and the continuation of HudMod: [i][url={support_link}]Patreon[/url][/i]
[/code]"
project_founder = &"Omar Mohammed Balita"
lead_developer = &"Omar Mohammed Balita"
developers = Array[String](["Malek Al-Ateeq", "Omar Mohammed Balita"])
